    },
    {
      "id": "cfa8f71bcea8951e9ec4bc7276acd758d7d280ce",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-05 06:10:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: (2 inline comments)\n\nI'm not against landing code incrementally, but I'd really like to see the patch that is using this code as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "a19b92bcda4ec4e0becc7bf7a5beb8d4df71f5d6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 212,
        "name": "Alexander Boyko",
        "email": "alexander.boyko@hpe.com",
        "username": "aboyko"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-05 06:52:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: (1 inline comment)\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "078916388433ab0f20b1bf2a06a430d8788e4085",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-14 14:21:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nHas any attempt been made to get this code landed upstream?  The PCLMUL crc32 patch was accepted upstream, and if you ran a performance comparison for this and included it into the commit message it would probably be accepted upstream as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "8792ae3a6bd42889fff129a64041c300e94fd2a5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-14 14:31:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe patch looks mostly ok, but it will need to be updated with the same exclusions for the Xeon Phi CPU as with the PCLMUL crc32 code. \n\nAlso, I don't think the one kernel test needs its own subdirectory, or is there some other benefit to this?\n\nThe other issue is the license of the code is not GPL. I have to check further what problem there is, if any, about including this in Lustre.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "3b629409e83ff3f175964d1e7eb04d9cb6bb5461",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-17 20:36:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nFor the record, it appears that the original Intel code is considered a 2-clause BSD license, so it is OK to be linked with GPL code.\n\nI still think it makes sense to submit this to the upstream kernel, and it can eventually be backported to the vendor kernels so that we don't have to keep this code around forever.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "eeb43f5445ae2ea3bfb3057a6fa88b6c93662112",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-26 01:23:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nDmitry, can you please check if this patch will break the Xeon Phi builds?  If I misunderstand it, and it does NOT break the Xeon Phi builds then I can remove my negative inspection.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "5fa53307c82eba56b8a4df9b5c3e7a541e786f19",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-07-15 13:33:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThis patch should be rebased. Current version based on master that is not supported Xeon Phi compilation. Therefore it's not aware about it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "e6b5d8ea4708efab316b4f427655ab5c9059737b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-07-16 13:32:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nAlso, could you move libcfs/libcfs/crc16_t10_asm.S under linux subdirectory to be more consistent?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "759bc3fdde1bb920b118600b320a593041d595c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-27 14:16:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nDmitry,\n\ndid you really think it's don't used on other OS? liblustre and Windows/Fuse clients uses it's also.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "09a98f0029c461e86573defc01bdb6ca63d0e14c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-07-29 10:15:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI think it's Linux specific because it's AT&T assembler syntax. This syntax is not supported by Microsoft compiler. Therefore you can compile it only on Unix systems with GAS or using Unix like environment like Cygwin.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "5b5ca88bf04140595b10129e47e40d6c598dd7bd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 212,
        "name": "Alexander Boyko",
        "email": "alexander.boyko@hpe.com",
        "username": "aboyko"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-28 17:17:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Abandoned\n\nI will not update this patch, cause I don`t see T10 progress.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    }
  ],
